092177,0.074581,0.081476,0.064698,0.05624,0.046979,0.034279]},{"section":6,"text":"First, I need to think about the possible causes of vertigo.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.078884,0.12016,0.13289,0.12684,0.1043,0.08102,0.074275,0.065959,0.056472,0.067261,0.046225,0.045707],"unified_progress":[0.086371,0.083706,0.088188,0.10261,0.098883,0.091241,0.093806,0.084598,0.075123,0.085787,0.061855,0.047826]},{"section":7,"text":"The key here is the description of the dizziness being positional\u2014specifically when moving from sitting to lying down with her head turned and below the horizontal plane.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.090683,0.14621,0.11845,0.099678,0.088582,0.087309,0.075889,0.076058,0.063374,0.05776,0.050233,0.045769],"unified_progress":[0.082332,0.11484,0.10394,0.097158,0.091391,0.090271,0.083132,0.086674,0.074614,0.067629,0.058746,0.049273]},{"section":8,"text":"That makes me think of Benign Paroxysmal Positional Vertigo (BPPV).","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.059625,0.099034,0.10495,0.10586,0.10215,0.094532,0.090134,0.083082,0.072689,0.073287,0.058812,0.055843],"unified_progress":[0.062583,0.075043,0.093274,0.09601,0.096415,0.10252,0.095356,0.091012,0.083429,0.081706,0.066859,0.05579]},{"section":9,"text":"The nystagmus observed during the maneuver is also a big clue because BPPV typically causes positional nystagmus.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054163,0.099811,0.10342,0.10126,0.096894,0.093249,0.089276,0.084964,0.078347,0.074843,0.06444,0.059339],"unified_progress":[0.052453,0.082757,0.090968,0.096894,0.097994,0.097502,0.093781,0.091962,0.086971,0.081464,0.069643,0.057611]},{"section":10,"text":"Let me recall the pathophysiology of BPPV.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047996,0.081536,0.093269,0.098456,0.098876,0.094013,0.091821,0.087936,0.083631,0.082704,0.071795,0.067966],"unified_progress":[0.064601,0.072181,0.083322,0.094954,0.095313,0.093874,0.094558,0.09107,0.08592,0.089166,0.073751,0.06129]},{"section":11,"text":"It's caused by loose otoconia in the semicircular canals, usually the posterior canal.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039136,0.075725,0.086591,0.095876,0.10054,0.10118,0.10035,0.093799,0.088738,0.083266,0.071376,0.063419],"unified_progress":[0.056431,0.068222,0.086382,0.097587,0.099688,0.10319,0.098373,0.094925,0.089237,0.081487,0.067118,0.057358]},{"section":12,"text":"When the head is moved into certain positions, these particles shift, stimulating the cupula and leading to the sensation of vertigo and nystagmus.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045385,0.084312,0.087238,0.091157,0.094778,0.097544,0.097358,0.094001,0.088856,0.08244,0.072521,0.064411],"unified_progress":[0.060883,0.075872,0.085448,0.091384,0.095324,0.099466,0.095175,0.094164,0.089698,0.082229,0.071155,0.059203]},{"section":13,"text":"The Dix-Hallpike maneuver is used to diagnose it, which involves moving the patient from sitting to lying with the head below the horizontal.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049953,0.090823,0.090837,0.091008,0.092246,0.095005,0.093463,0.091496,0.087558,0.0801,0.071793,0.065717],"unified_progress":[0.064575,0.081908,0.088892,0.092933,0.095014,0.096598,0.092707,0.091455,0.087305,0.078828,0.069252,0.060534]},{"section":14,"text":"The patient's symptoms match this: positional vertigo, brief episodes, and the\u8bf1\u53d1 of nystagmus during the maneuver.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056712,0.10101,0.094716,0.088473,0.087447,0.090674,0.088615,0.089881,0.084329,0.078915,0.073074,0.066155],"unified_progress":[0.068757,0.091665,0.089747,0.089993,0.090752,0.092417,0.08866,0.090774,0.085776,0.079786,0.071431,0.060241]},{"section":15,"text":"Other possibilities to consider: Maybe vestibular neuritis, but that usually presents with continuous vertigo, not positional, and often has associated hearing loss or tinnitus.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02768,0.062775,0.07696,0.086859,0.093618,0.097062,0.10363,0.1031,0.09956,0.096257,0.087546,0.064945],"unified_progress":[0.031877,0.061378,0.078001,0.085456,0.096146,0.099482,0.10136,0.10378,0.10125,0.10283,0.083654,0.054787]},{"section":16,"text":"Labyrinthitis could be a contender, but again, it's more about inflammation with hearing symptoms and maybe fever, which she doesn't have.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.017248,0.047702,0.064733,0.077256,0.086622,0.094718,0.10729,0.11232,0.11164,0.10994,0.1019,0.068625],"unified_progress":[0.023059,0.051433,0.068734,0.077924,0.091706,0.096034,0.10269,0.11171,0.11145,0.12018,0.092999,0.052084]},{"section":17,"text":"Meniere's disease has episodes of vertigo lasting hours, along with hearing loss and ear fullness.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023512,0.056123,0.069118,0.081247,0.091355,0.098801,0.10636,0.10742,0.10344,0.10228,0.090884,0.069454],"unified_progress":[0.030098,0.055622,0.071534,0.083207,0.092736,0.10309,0.1039,0.10897,0.10653,0.10621,0.085158,0.052944]},{"section":18,"text":"Since her episodes are brief and positional, that's less likely.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.021956,0.053814,0.068822,0.078982,0.086557,0.09318,0.10288,0.10703,0.10731,0.10544,0.099376,0.07465],"unified_progress":[0.037538,0.055164,0.068466,0.07746,0.088857,0.092633,0.098811,0.1062,0.1062,0.11558,0.091918,0.061175]},{"section":19,"text":"She doesn't have any upper respiratory symptoms, so maybe not related to a recent infection causing labyrinthitis.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026998,0.060754,0.073101,0.081584,0.089407,0.098184,0.10083,0.10364,0.10283,0.10081,0.091416,0.07044],"unified_progress":[0.052307,0.084193,0.083725,0.084673,0.088995,0.091721,0.094179,0.09711,0.094755,0.094487,0.079002,0.054851]},{"section":20,"text":"No medications, so no ototoxic drugs.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030875,0.06678,0.079262,0.086577,0.09244,0.10013,0.099899,0.10041,0.097242,0.095001,0.085755,0.065638],"unified_progress":[0.064956,0.097915,0.093455,0.093246,0.092666,0.092811,0.090231,0.091818,0.084806,0.080736,0.068333,0.049028]},{"section":21,"text":"The absence of fever also makes infectious causes less likely.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023535,0.05691,0.073055,0.082889,0.089617,0.09474,0.10233,0.10358,0.10277,0.10181,0.095634,0.073126],"unified_progress":[0.039172,0.06813,0.078663,0.086355,0.095609,0.095298,0.098955,0.10054,0.097869,0.099672,0.083011,0.056721]},{"section":22,"text":"The key here is the positional component and the nystagmus on Dix-Hallpike, which points strongly to BPPV.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027583,0.060393,0.074844,0.082398,0.08657,0.088991,0.092725,0.093545,0.096821,0.099008,0.097338,0.099785],"unified_progress":[0.033489,0.056768,0.069501,0.080375,0.086266,0.091667,0.09653,0.096173,0.098329,0.099478,0.098491,0.092932]},{"section":23,"text":"I don't see any red flags here that would suggest a central cause like a stroke or multiple sclerosis, since there's no neurological deficits mentioned, and the symptoms are so positionally triggered.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024709,0.058077,0.071626,0.080136,0.08626,0.091695,0.099567,0.10301,0.10405,0.10326,0.097594,0.080009],"unified_progress":[0.027579,0.055692,0.069635,0.078688,0.089015,0.092478,0.098038,0.1042,0.10545,0.11152,0.097031,0.070678]},{"section":24,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is BPPV, specifically posterior semicircular canal involvement given the typical presentation with the Dix-Hallpike maneuver.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029067,0.056846,0.065682,0.072653,0.077829,0.082909,0.087725,0.090279,0.097042,0.096838,0.10209,0.14105],"unified_progress":[0.030906,0.043787,0.05394,0.064233,0.069822,0.07799,0.082054,0.088614,0.096286,0.10059,0.12627,0.16551]}]}}